# m6_damage_number_tiers.shot — M6 P04
#
# Single-process color-tier visual test for the damage-number feature.
# Drives one stationary Heavy dummy through five sequential damage
# events, one per tier, using the new `damage` shotmode directive.
# Each event spawns a flying glyph (FX_DAMAGE_NUMBER) that flies out
# from the chest, falls under gravity, bounces ≤2 times on the floor
# with a metallic *tink*, and fades.
#
# Tier mapping (per src/particle.c::g_dmg_tier):
#   5    → DMG_TIER_LIGHT  (pale yellow, 10 px)
#   20   → DMG_TIER_NORMAL (yellow,      12 px)
#   45   → DMG_TIER_MEDIUM (orange,      14 px)
#   75   → DMG_TIER_HEAVY  (red-orange,  16 px)
#   150  → DMG_TIER_CRIT   (bright red,  18 px)
#
# Heavy chassis HP = 220 + ~75 absorbed by Heavy armor; total damage
# 5+20+45+75+150 = 295 leaves the dummy alive through every spawn.
# Per-shot perp_sign + cone-jitter at spawn (particle.c::fx_spawn_
# damage_number) fans the five glyphs out into different directions
# so they don't visually stack.
#
# Run:
#   ./soldut --shot tests/shots/m6_damage_number_tiers.shot
# Output:
#   build/shots/m6_damage_number_tiers/*.png
#   build/shots/m6_damage_number_tiers/tiers.png  (3-col contact sheet)
#
# Verification (manual visual review on the contact sheet):
#   - All 5 colors read distinctly (LIGHT pale-yellow → CRIT bright-red).
#   - Spew arcs are visibly different magnitudes (CRIT spews farther than
#     LIGHT; bigger glyphs = more damage gradient holds).
#   - Settled frame shows numbers near/on the floor with at most 2
#     bounces visible (pin_limb cap from §7).

window 1280 720
seed 1 1
out build/shots/m6_damage_number_tiers
map slipstream
no_parallax
loadout Trooper "Pulse Rifle" Sidearm Light Standard

# Slipstream basement_ceil top y=1216 → spawn pelvis 40 above = 1176.
# Player at left of frame; one Heavy dummy 200 px to the right.
# Heavy chassis HP=220 (no armor) > total 295 dmg dispatched, but
# we deliberately let the dummy die after the 4th hit so the spec's
# "kill via damage tier" beat is also exercised — the kill blow
# itself doesn't get special treatment, just the appropriate tier
# color (CRIT for 150).
spawn_at 1500 1176
mouse 1180 360

# Auto-dummy (mech_id=1) spawns at slipstream's team-2 spawn point,
# off-screen. The Heavy I add here is mech_id=2 — the one I drive.
extra_chassis Heavy 1700 1176

# Let the Verlet solver settle both chassis onto their feet.
at 30 shot pre_damage

# Five damage events at 5-tick intervals — enough spacing that each
# spawn fires on its own tick (HIT_FLASH timer doesn't bleed) but
# tight enough that midflight + settled frames capture all five
# glyphs simultaneously airborne / on the floor.
at 35 damage 2 CHEST 5      # LIGHT
at 40 damage 2 CHEST 20     # NORMAL
at 45 damage 2 CHEST 45     # MEDIUM
at 50 damage 2 CHEST 75     # HEAVY
at 55 damage 2 CHEST 150    # CRIT

# Three captures along the spew → bounce → fade arc.
at 60  shot t005_spawn         # ~0.08 s after last spawn — fresh spew, all 5 airborne
at 90  shot t035_midflight     # ~0.58 s — midflight, first bounces visible
at 150 shot t095_settled       # ~1.58 s — most settled, mid-fade tail

# Ten contact-sheet cells (4 wide × 3 tall) is overkill for 4 frames —
# 4-col layout gives a clean horizontal strip of 4 frames in row 1.
contact_sheet tiers cols 4 cell 480 270

at 200 end
